commit.message:
Use simplified code block syntax in README

ELPA's markdown formatter doesn't support fenced code blocks -- and
evidently won't any time soon.
Increment version to fix licensing issue in build

Minor README formatting updates

Mostly hard-wrapping. I'd like to see what this looks like before
considering removing all the language tags from code blocks. Ideally,
we could just find a way to support the syntax in ELPA's renderer.
Mark copyright as now held by the FSF
Apply some cleanup patches from Stefan
Update MELPA badge to new url
Add 'clean' target

commit.message: Require subr-x for thread-last in examples.el
More docstrings
Change macro syntax to be slightly more natural
Make sure 'plain' cons cell keys are not cons cells themselves
Add documentation

Response form should mirror input form when using macros

This does introduce an extra level of parentheses when writing the
queries, but modern Lisp editors should make this trivial compared to
the gains in actually understanding the code.
Correct capitalization
Add support for specifying GraphQL lists using Lisp vector syntax
